body:
I don’t think I’ll be able to accept season 8 of GOT it Jon Snow doesn’t get to mount a dragon at least once.

Mainly because I want to see Daenerys’s reaction when she sees Jon on it. Especially if she has no idea about his Targaryen ancestry. But also, how cool would that look?

summary: A very good friend of mine lives across the pond and we have a lot of time difference. Lucky for me, he doesn’t sleep much and...
body:
A song of ice and fire: early morning conversations.

A very good friend of mine lives across the pond and we have a lot of time difference. Lucky for me, he doesn’t sleep much and we get to talk about the most random stuff at the oddest hours. I was at work when he texted me. It was around 2 am his time. We talked about the polar vortex, holiday destinations, and harassing anon messages I’ve been receiving. Finally, I moved to a more important topic: Game of Thrones.

Me: I started rewatching GoT. I appreciate it even more this time.

Him: Favourite character?

Me: Tyrion. He’s intelligent.

Him: Interesting. It’s the only reason he’s alive.

Me: I also like how Jaime evolved for the better, but I may be a bit biased because he’s hot.

Him: Losing his hand may have been the best thing for him. Complete tyrant if that wouldn’t have happened. How about the girls?

Me: I agree. Sansa represents the kind of girls I don’t like at all. Girls whose only purpose in life is to get a husband.

Him: No disagreement from me on that front. Plastic girls. Dolls. Pick me, pick me.

Me: Daenerys is very cool. And she has dragons.

Him: And wants to ride her nephew or was he her cousin?

Me: Lol. Nephew.

Him: I must rewatch it now. Details and connections are blurry. I’m not on your level in this conversation, but I love it.

Then I sent him the below picture.

Him: It’s 4 am and you’ve already made my day. Thank you for that. 😂

I forgot to tell him that I think Jon Snow looks like him.
